# Fixtures and helpers

## When to use what

| Layer | Use when | Location |
|-------|----------|----------|
| **Fixture** | Setup + **teardown** (browser context) | `src/fixtures/` |
| **Helper** | Stateless flow reused by specs / doc generator | `src/test-helpers/` |
| **POM** | UI surface interactions | `src/pages/` |

---

## Frontend — [fe-fixtures.ts](../../src/fixtures/fe-fixtures.ts)

| Fixture | Behavior |
|---------|----------|
| `loginPage` | `goto('/')` → `LoginPage` instance |
| `inventoryPage` | `goto('/')` → login as `standard_user` → `InventoryPage` |

```typescript
loginPage: async ({ page }, use) => {
  await page.goto('/');
  await use(new LoginPage(page));
},

inventoryPage: async ({ page }, use) => {
  await page.goto('/');
  const inventory = await new LoginPage(page).login(
    users.standard.username,
    users.standard.password,
  );
  await use(inventory);
},
```

Test data: [`saucedemo-users.json`](../../src/data/input-data/saucedemo-users.json), [`checkout-data.json`](../../src/data/input-data/checkout-data.json) via [`input-data.ts`](../../src/config/input-data.ts).

---

## Authoring pattern

```typescript
myFixture: async ({ page }, use) => {
  await setup(page);
  await use(resource);
  await teardown(page);
},
```

Split new domains into separate fixture files when `fe-fixtures` grows.
